This folder contains CFD data for the test case (LID Driven Cavity) used in the paper 
“Sparse-Supervised Hybrid Parameterized Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Incompressible Flows Across Reynolds Numbers.”
The data were generated using OpenFOAM 12 and validated against reference data from the literature by Cortes and Miller (1993).
Each CSV file is named according to the corresponding Reynolds number (for example, DataRe100.csv corresponds to Re = 100).
Every file contains five columns: x, y, u, v, and p.
For the pure PINN approach, the entire dataset is used for validation. 
For the hybrid PINN approach, sparse data in the range 750 < Re < 850 are used during training, 
while the remaining data are employed to validate the trained hybrid PINN model.
